Human Rights Watch criticized China's forced resettlements in Tibet and surrounding areas, urging Beijing to halt the process until a review system is established.
Tibetans have been forced to abandon their traditional way of life, with herders being required to sell their livestock and move into new townships.
The government's efforts to combat desertification have led to the displacement of farmers in Gansu province.
Despite conservation projects, soil erosion remains a significant issue, impacting agricultural productivity.
China aims to address soil erosion through various initiatives, including banning farming on steep hillsides and promoting terracing to prevent further degradation.
